<title>USA: TABLE - Veritas Q2 eps up excluding charges.</title>
<headline>TABLE - Veritas Q2 eps up excluding charges.</headline>
<dateline>MOUNTAIN VIEW, Calif. 1997-07-16</dateline>
<text>
<p>Three Months Ended</p>
<p>							  June 30,</p>
<p>							  1997	 1996</p>
<p> Total revenue				  $28,934	 $17,890</p>
<p> Pro forma operating income		   6,642	   3,692</p>
<p> Pro forma income before taxes		7,477	   4,179</p>
<p> Pro forma net income			   6,131	   3,761</p>
<p> Pro forma net income per share		0.28	    0.18</p>
<p> Shares used in per share computation    21,688	  20,607</p>
<p>							  Six Months Ended</p>
<p>							     June 30,</p>
<p>							   1997	 1996</p>
<p> Total revenue				  $54,544	 $33,188</p>
<p> Pro forma operating income		  12,291	   6,755</p>
<p> Pro forma income before taxes	     13,961	   7,419</p>
<p> Pro forma net income			  11,448	   6,455</p>
<p> Pro forma net income per share		0.53	    0.32</p>
<p> Shares used in per share computation    21,646	  20,156</p>
<p>		     (In thousands, except per share data)</p>
<p>NOTE: Company's full name is VERITAS Software Corp.</p>
<p>Date for 1997 exclude the write-off of $8.5 million for one-time charges related to the merger with OpenVision Technologies Inc.</p>
<p>Data for 1996 exclude the write-off of $2.2 million for the purchase of ACSC.</p>
<p>Pro forma fully taxed earnings per share for the quarter were $0.22, compared to $0.13 for the year-ago period, also excluding these charges.</p>
<p>Including charges, net loss for the quarter was $1.7 million, or $0.08 per share, compared with net earnings of $1.6 million, or $0.08 per share, for the year-ago period.</p>
